29MediaChannel::MediaChannel(const MediaConfig& config,
30 TaskQueueBase* network_thread)
31 : enable_dscp_(config.enable_dscp),
32 network_safety_(PendingTaskSafetyFlag::CreateDetachedInactive()),
33 network_thread_(network_thread) {}
34
35MediaChannel::MediaChannel(TaskQueueBase* network_thread)
36 : enable_dscp_(false),
37 network_safety_(PendingTaskSafetyFlag::CreateDetachedInactive()),
38 network_thread_(network_thread) {}

40MediaChannel::~MediaChannel() {
41 RTC_DCHECK(!network_interface_);
42}
43
44void MediaChannel::SetInterface(NetworkInterface* iface) {
45 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
46 iface ? network_safety_->SetAlive() : network_safety_->SetNotAlive();
47 network_interface_ = iface;
48 UpdateDscp();
49}

69bool MediaChannel::SendPacket(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer* packet,
70 const rtc::PacketOptions& options) {
71 return DoSendPacket(packet, false, options);
72}
73
74bool MediaChannel::SendRtcp(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer* packet,
75 const rtc::PacketOptions& options) {
76 return DoSendPacket(packet, true, options);
77}

79int MediaChannel::SetOption(NetworkInterface::SocketType type,
80 rtc::Socket::Option opt,
81 int option) {
82 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
83 return SetOptionLocked(type, opt, option);
84}

86// Corresponds to the SDP attribute extmap-allow-mixed, see RFC8285.
87// Set to true if it's allowed to mix one- and two-byte RTP header extensions
88// in the same stream. The setter and getter must only be called from
89// worker_thread.
90void MediaChannel::SetExtmapAllowMixed(bool extmap_allow_mixed) {
91 extmap_allow_mixed_ = extmap_allow_mixed;
92}

94bool MediaChannel::ExtmapAllowMixed() const {
95 return extmap_allow_mixed_;
96}

106int MediaChannel::SetOptionLocked(NetworkInterface::SocketType type,
107 rtc::Socket::Option opt,
108 int option) {
109 if (!network_interface_)
110 return -1;
111 return network_interface_->SetOption(type, opt, option);
112}

114bool MediaChannel::DscpEnabled() const {
115 return enable_dscp_;
116}
117
118// This is the DSCP value used for both RTP and RTCP channels if DSCP is
119// enabled. It can be changed at any time via |SetPreferredDscp|.
120rtc::DiffServCodePoint MediaChannel::PreferredDscp() const {
121 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
122 return preferred_dscp_;
123}
124
125void MediaChannel::SetPreferredDscp(rtc::DiffServCodePoint new_dscp) {
126 if (!network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
127 // This is currently the common path as the derived channel classes
128 // get called on the worker thread. There are still some tests though
129 // that call directly on the network thread.
130 network_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
131 network_safety_, [this, new_dscp]() { SetPreferredDscp(new_dscp); }));
132 return;
133 }
134
135 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
136 if (new_dscp == preferred_dscp_)
137 return;
138
139 preferred_dscp_ = new_dscp;
140 UpdateDscp();
141}
142
143rtc::scoped_refptr<PendingTaskSafetyFlag> MediaChannel::network_safety() {
144 return network_safety_;
145}
146
147void MediaChannel::UpdateDscp() {
148 rtc::DiffServCodePoint value =
149 enable_dscp_ ? preferred_dscp_ : rtc::DSCP_DEFAULT;
150 int ret =
151 SetOptionLocked(NetworkInterface::ST_RTP, rtc::Socket::OPT_DSCP, value);
152 if (ret == 0)
153 SetOptionLocked(NetworkInterface::ST_RTCP, rtc::Socket::OPT_DSCP, value);
154}
155
156bool MediaChannel::DoSendPacket(rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer* packet,
157 bool rtcp,
158 const rtc::PacketOptions& options) {
159 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
160 if (!network_interface_)
161 return false;
162
163 return (!rtcp) ? network_interface_->SendPacket(packet, options)
164 : network_interface_->SendRtcp(packet, options);
165}
166
167void MediaChannel::SendRtp(const uint8_t* data,
168 size_t len,
169 const webrtc::PacketOptions& options) {
170 auto send =
171 [this, packet_id = options.packet_id,
172 included_in_feedback = options.included_in_feedback,
173 included_in_allocation = options.included_in_allocation,
174 packet = rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer(data, len, kMaxRtpPacketLen)]() mutable {
175 rtc::PacketOptions rtc_options;
176 rtc_options.packet_id = packet_id;
177 if (DscpEnabled()) {
178 rtc_options.dscp = PreferredDscp();
179 }
180 rtc_options.info_signaled_after_sent.included_in_feedback =
181 included_in_feedback;
182 rtc_options.info_signaled_after_sent.included_in_allocation =
183 included_in_allocation;
184 SendPacket(&packet, rtc_options);
185 };
186
187 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): ModuleRtpRtcpImpl2 and related classes (e.g.
188 // RTCPSender) aren't aware of the network thread and may trigger calls to
189 // this function from different threads. Update those classes to keep
190 // network traffic on the network thread.
191 if (network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
192 send();
193 } else {
194 network_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(network_safety_, std::move(send)));
195 }
196}
197
198void MediaChannel::SendRtcp(const uint8_t* data, size_t len) {
199 auto send = [this, packet = rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer(
200 data, len, kMaxRtpPacketLen)]() mutable {
201 rtc::PacketOptions rtc_options;
202 if (DscpEnabled()) {
203 rtc_options.dscp = PreferredDscp();
204 }
205 SendRtcp(&packet, rtc_options);
206 };
207
208 if (network_thread_->IsCurrent()) {
209 send();
210 } else {
211 network_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(network_safety_, std::move(send)));
212 }
213}
